<div class="pub">

  












  

  
  
  
<div class="article-container pt-3">
  <h1>Abordagens para reconfiguração de sistemas de tempo real com QoS e restrições de energia e temperatura</h1>

  

  
    


<div class="article-metadata">

  
  
  
  
  <div>
    

  <span >
      Rı́ad Mattos Nassiffe</span>, <span >
       others</span>
  </div>
  
  

  
  <span class="article-date">
    
    
      
    
    January 2015
  </span>
  

  

  

  
  
  
  
  
  

  
  

</div>

    




<div class="btn-links mb-3">
  
  








  





<a href="#" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-page-header js-cite-modal"
        data-filename="/repositorio.ufsc.br/xmlui/handle/123456789/cite.bib">
  Cite
</a>















</div>


  
</div>



  <div class="article-container">

    
    <h3>Abstract</h3>
    <p class="pub-abstract">This thesis proposes a framework for dynamic reconfiguration, value-based processor resource allocation in multi-modal or not real-time applications, under schedulability, energy consumption and temperature constraints. The framework is suitable for critical and soft real-time adaptive embedded systems which need guarantees of energy savings. The dynamic allocation is formulated as a discrete and continuous (convex and piecewise linear) optimization problem for which efficients algorithms were tested. Although the discrete problem is NP-Hard, the others have efficient solution and numerical analysis and simulations have shown that the used algorithms and models achieves very good results, with low computational cost.</p>
    

    
    
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-1"></div>
      <div class="col-md-10">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-12 col-md-3 pub-row-heading">Type</div>
          <div class="col-12 col-md-9">
            <a href="/publication/#7">
              Thesis
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-1"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="d-md-none space-below"></div>
    

    

